# LogicN Contract Architecture & Complete Mediation Model

Integrating the newly established architectural categories with the complete language primitives provides a unified view of the LogicN `contract {}` block. This block functions as the **Security and Operations Manifest** for every workflow isolate, establishing complete mediation across twelve distinct pillars of high-assurance software verification.

---

## The 12-Category Complete Mediation Model

By extending the core language mechanics to handle multi-tenant, zero-trust cloud deployment, the platform taxonomy expands into a comprehensive 12-category matrix:

| Category | Primary Architectural Focus | Language Primitive | Structural Engineering Responsibility |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Syntax** | Grammar rules, type signatures, structural blocks, and language keywords. | `types {}`, `flow`, `step` | Establishes static type shapes, algebraic variants, and grammar layout rules required by the flow context. |
| **Contract** | Human- and machine-readable intent specifications, expectations, and safety proofs. | `intent {}`, `invariant {}` | Houses intent assertions and formal verification statements checked at both compile time and runtime. |
| **Effect** | Declared out-of-bounds mutations, state writes, and structural side effects. | `effects {}` | Mandates upfront declaration of targeted environment state changes (e.g., `ledger.mutate`). |
| **Capability** | Strongly typed, non-string resource permissions mapped to declarative host channels. | `authority {}`, `targets {}` | Maps resource authorizations directly onto explicit, variant-backed capability configurations, eliminating text wildcards. |
| **Isolation** | Shared-nothing memory allocation boundaries, JIT guard pages, and OS containment wrappers. | `limits {}` | Restricts ephemeral memory allocations (e.g., 4MB ceilings), zero-pointer sharing, and host virtual environments. |
| **Monotonic** | State decay rules ensuring privilege reduction over execution time via CAS atomicity. | *(Implicit)* | Ensures the Dynamic Posture Matrix ($V_{\text{DPM}}$) updates unidirectionally during faults, preventing privilege escalation. |
| **AI Authoring** | Machine-readable context parsing rules, documentation layout targets, and compliance generation. | *(Implicit)* | Controls structured artifact emissions like `app.ai-guide.md` to feed LLM code-generation tools safe context. |
| **Process** | Isolate scheduling loops, deterministic execution paths, and asynchronous step trees. | `request {}`, `response {}` | Formulates the I/O payload boundaries and step-to-step messaging boundaries across execution threads. |
| **Economics 🌟** | Resource cost-containment, usage leases, outbound consumption thresholds, and monetization metrics. | `economics {}` | Regulates financial processing caps, upstream credit spending, and volume-based loop execution boundaries. |
| **Identity 🌟** | Cryptographic provenance tracking, binary integrity mapping, and post-quantum attestation. | *(Manifest)* | Enforces signature evaluation (`ML-DSA-65`) and content tracking via compilation manifest proofs (`.lmanifest`). |
| **Auditability 🌟** | Tamper-evident execution trail formulation and un-bypassable text stream scrubbing. | `privacy {}`, `secrets {}`, `audit {}` | Registers tracking tokens within the Secret Sink Monitor and configures framing rules for signed Epilogue Receipts. |
| **Lifecycle 🌟** | Structural state updates, version deprecation, temporal constraints, and platform epoch management. | *(Policy)* | Manages the atomic migration of long-running contract definitions and runtime initialization sequences. |

